]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<figure><img src="https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-50.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="The best drones of 2026 so far and how much you can get them for in Thailand | Thaiger" style="margin-bottom: 15px;" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-50.jpg 1280w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-50-300x169.jpg 300w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-50-820x461.jpg 820w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-50-768x432.jpg 768w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-50-390x220.jpg 390w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" width="1280" height="720" /><figcaption>The best drones of 2026 so far and how much you can get them for in Thailand<span class="copyright">Legacy</span></figcaption></figure><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1280" height="720" src="https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-50.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="The best drones of 2026 so far and how much you can get them for in Thailand | Thaiger" style="float:right; margin:0 0 10px 10px;" srcset="https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-50.jpg 1280w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-50-300x169.jpg 300w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-50-820x461.jpg 820w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-50-768x432.jpg 768w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-50-390x220.jpg 390w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">DJI&#8217;s release wave over the past twelve months has reset the consumer drone market almost entirely. The Mavic 4 Pro, Mini 5 Pro, Avata 360, and Neo 2 have all landed, reviewers have had time to test them properly, and a clear consensus has formed. Cross-referencing a dozen major 2026 buyer&#8217;s guides, Tom&#8217;s Guide, TechRadar, Engadget, PCMag, DroneDJ, DroneXL, Digital Camera World and others, produces a remarkably tight agreement on which drones are worth buying and which categories they lead.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">This guide summarises that consensus and then translates it into real Thai baht pricing, because Thailand is one of the few markets where the full 2026 DJI lineup is officially on sale with local warranty.</p>
<h2 class="text-text-100 mt-3 -mb-1 text-[1.125rem] font-bold">What the reviewers agree on</h2>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">The table below shows how many of the twelve major review sources back each drone, and which category it typically wins. When ten out of twelve independent reviewers land on the same drone as the best camera pick, that is a real signal.</p>
