					<description><![CDATA[<p>Thai residents in Chachoengsao sought help for a 13 year old Burmese girl after alleging she had been repeatedly abused by her mother at their home. The case came to public attention after neighbours contacted social media influencer Chalida “Ton Or” Palamart to assist the girl, identified as Namwhan. Officials from the Chachoengsao Provincial Shelter &#8230;</p>
<p>The story <a href="https://thethaiger.com/news/central-thailand/burmese-girl-in-chachoengsao-rescued-after-abuses-by-mother">Thai neighbours seeks help for Burmese girl abused by mother</a> as seen on <a href="https://thethaiger.com/">Thaiger News</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<figure><img src="https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Thaiger-News-Cover-Picture-with-Template-2026-05-13T153648.275.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="Thai neighbours seeks help for Burmese girl abused by mother | Thaiger" style="margin-bottom: 15px;" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Thaiger-News-Cover-Picture-with-Template-2026-05-13T153648.275.jpg 1280w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Thaiger-News-Cover-Picture-with-Template-2026-05-13T153648.275-300x169.jpg 300w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Thaiger-News-Cover-Picture-with-Template-2026-05-13T153648.275-820x461.jpg 820w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Thaiger-News-Cover-Picture-with-Template-2026-05-13T153648.275-768x432.jpg 768w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Thaiger-News-Cover-Picture-with-Template-2026-05-13T153648.275-390x220.jpg 390w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" width="1280" height="720" /><figcaption>Thai neighbours seeks help for Burmese girl abused by mother<span class="copyright">Legacy</span></figcaption></figure><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1280" height="720" src="https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Thaiger-News-Cover-Picture-with-Template-2026-05-13T153648.275.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="Thai neighbours seeks help for Burmese girl abused by mother | Thaiger" style="float:right; margin:0 0 10px 10px;" srcset="https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Thaiger-News-Cover-Picture-with-Template-2026-05-13T153648.275.jpg 1280w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Thaiger-News-Cover-Picture-with-Template-2026-05-13T153648.275-300x169.jpg 300w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Thaiger-News-Cover-Picture-with-Template-2026-05-13T153648.275-820x461.jpg 820w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Thaiger-News-Cover-Picture-with-Template-2026-05-13T153648.275-768x432.jpg 768w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Thaiger-News-Cover-Picture-with-Template-2026-05-13T153648.275-390x220.jpg 390w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /><p>Thai residents in Chachoengsao sought help for a<strong> 13 year old Burmese girl</strong> after alleging she had been <strong>repeatedly <a href="https://thethaiger.com/news/national/udon-thani-mother-forces-thai-british-girl-into-abuse-by-stepfather" target="_blank" rel="noopener">abused</a></strong><a href="https://thethaiger.com/news/national/udon-thani-mother-forces-thai-british-girl-into-abuse-by-stepfather"> by her <strong>mother</strong></a> at their home.</p>
<p>The case came to public attention after neighbours contacted social media influencer Chalida “Ton Or” Palamart to assist the girl, identified as Namwhan. Officials from the Chachoengsao Provincial Shelter for Children and Family accompanied Ton Or to the family’s home yesterday, May 12.</p>
<p>During the visit, Ton Or observed that Namwhan had a shaved head and visible injuries to her head and ears. Bruises and marks were also reportedly seen on several parts of her body.</p>
<p>The girl initially refused to speak while her mother was present. Officials later escorted her away from the house, where she eventually described ongoing abuse inside the home.</p>
<figure id="attachment_1002598" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-1002598" style="width: 1280px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-1002598" src="https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Thaiger-Cover-Picture-2026-05-13T153546.134.jpg" alt="Burmese girl rescued from abusive mother in Chachoengsao" width="1280" height="720" srcset="https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Thaiger-Cover-Picture-2026-05-13T153546.134.jpg 1280w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Thaiger-Cover-Picture-2026-05-13T153546.134-300x169.jpg 300w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Thaiger-Cover-Picture-2026-05-13T153546.134-820x461.jpg 820w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Thaiger-Cover-Picture-2026-05-13T153546.134-768x432.jpg 768w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Thaiger-Cover-Picture-2026-05-13T153546.134-390x220.jpg 390w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-1002598" class="wp-caption-text">Photo via Facebook/ <a href="https://www.facebook.com/reel/1517338566726190" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">ต้นอ้อ เป็นหนึ่ง</a></figcaption></figure>
<p>According to Namwhan, she has two older sisters, but she was the only child subjected to violence. She alleged that her mother regularly beat her, <a href="https://thethaiger.com/news/bangkok/bangkok-transwoman-forced-to-shave-hairs-for-quran-insult" target="_blank" rel="noopener">shaved her hair</a>, and sometimes gave her spoiled food to eat. The girl also claimed she was often limited to one meal per day and, on some occasions, was not given food at all.</p>
<p>Namwhan stated that injuries to her ears occurred when her mother attempted to cut them with scissors. She also showed officials a fresh wound that she said had been caused shortly before Ton Or arrived.</p>
<p>The mother denied the allegations during questioning, though she admitted to disciplining her daughter physically because she considered the child stubborn, but denied seriously abusing her. She claimed marks on Namwhan’s body were caused by food allergies rather than violence.</p>
<p>Ton Or later shared with her followers on social media that she was distressed after hearing the girl say she <a href="https://thethaiger.com/news/national/missing-burmese-girl-rescued-but-rejects-parents-over-alleged-abuse" target="_blank" rel="noopener">no longer wanted to remain with her family</a> because she feared being abused to death.</p>
<figure id="attachment_1002597" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-1002597" style="width: 1280px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-1002597" src="https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Thaiger-Cover-Picture-2026-05-13T153610.080.jpg" alt="Burmese mother denies abusing daughter" width="1280" height="720" srcset="https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Thaiger-Cover-Picture-2026-05-13T153610.080.jpg 1280w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Thaiger-Cover-Picture-2026-05-13T153610.080-300x169.jpg 300w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Thaiger-Cover-Picture-2026-05-13T153610.080-820x461.jpg 820w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Thaiger-Cover-Picture-2026-05-13T153610.080-768x432.jpg 768w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Thaiger-Cover-Picture-2026-05-13T153610.080-390x220.jpg 390w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-1002597" class="wp-caption-text">Photo via Facebook/ <a href="https://www.facebook.com/reel/1517338566726190" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">ต้นอ้อ เป็นหนึ่ง</a></figcaption></figure>
<p>Despite the violence, Namwhan told Ton Or that she still hoped to work in the future and support her mother financially, believing she might eventually receive the same affection shown to her siblings.</p>
<p>Officials placed the girl under the temporary protection of the Chachoengsao Provincial Shelter for Children and Family as part of the initial response to the abuse case.</p>
<p>According to Ton Or, the shelter is legally permitted to care for the child for only three months and has to return her to the family. Both Ton Or and the officials are now considering additional protective measures and long-term support options after that period expires.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><iframe loading="lazy" style="border: none; overflow: hidden;" src="https://www.facebook.com/plugins/video.php?height=476&amp;href=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2Freel%2F1517338566726190%2F&amp;show_text=false&amp;width=267&amp;t=0" width="267" height="476" frameborder="0" scrolling="no" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></p>
<p>The story <a href="https://thethaiger.com/news/central-thailand/burmese-girl-in-chachoengsao-rescued-after-abuses-by-mother">Thai neighbours seeks help for Burmese girl abused by mother</a> as seen on <a href="https://thethaiger.com/">Thaiger News</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
			</item>
		<item>
		<title>Thailand eases foreign business red tape in eight sectors to cut regulatory overlap</title>
		<link>https://thethaiger.com/news/business/thailand-eases-foreign-business-rules-in-eight-sectors</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Ryan Turner]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Wed, 13 May 2026 08:15:27 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Business News]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Economy News]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Business]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Thai cabinet]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Thai law]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://thethaiger.com/?p=1002562</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Thailand&#8217;s Cabinet has approved in principle two pieces of draft subordinate legislation under the Foreign Business Act 1999, exempting eight service business categories from the requirement to obtain a foreign business licence, the government announced on May 12. Deputy Government Spokesperson for the Prime Minister&#8217;s Office, Patdarasm Thongsaluaykorn, announced the Cabinet meeting. The two instruments, &#8230;</p>
<p>The story <a href="https://thethaiger.com/news/business/thailand-eases-foreign-business-rules-in-eight-sectors">Thailand eases foreign business red tape in eight sectors to cut regulatory overlap</a> as seen on <a href="https://thethaiger.com/">Thaiger News</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<figure><img src="https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/thailand-foreign-business-1.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="Thailand eases foreign business red tape in eight sectors to cut regulatory overlap | Thaiger" style="margin-bottom: 15px;" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/thailand-foreign-business-1.jpg 1280w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/thailand-foreign-business-1-300x169.jpg 300w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/thailand-foreign-business-1-820x461.jpg 820w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/thailand-foreign-business-1-768x432.jpg 768w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/thailand-foreign-business-1-390x220.jpg 390w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" width="1280" height="720" /><figcaption>Thailand eases foreign business red tape in eight sectors to cut regulatory overlap<span class="copyright">Legacy</span></figcaption></figure><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1280" height="720" src="https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/thailand-foreign-business-1.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="Thailand eases foreign business red tape in eight sectors to cut regulatory overlap | Thaiger" style="float:right; margin:0 0 10px 10px;" srcset="https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/thailand-foreign-business-1.jpg 1280w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/thailand-foreign-business-1-300x169.jpg 300w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/thailand-foreign-business-1-820x461.jpg 820w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/thailand-foreign-business-1-768x432.jpg 768w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/thailand-foreign-business-1-390x220.jpg 390w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Thailand&#8217;s <strong>Cabinet</strong> has approved in principle two pieces of draft subordinate legislation under the <strong>Foreign Business Act 1999</strong>, <strong>exempting eight service business</strong> categories from the requirement to obtain a <a href="https://thethaiger.com/news/business/thailand-to-ease-foreign-business-rules-boosting-investment-appeal" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>foreign business licence</strong></a>, the government announced on May 12.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Deputy Government Spokesperson for the Prime Minister&#8217;s Office, Patdarasm Thongsaluaykorn, announced the Cabinet meeting. The two instruments, a draft royal decree and a draft ministerial regulation, are designed to reduce duplication in regulatory procedures and bring oversight in line with the current economic environment.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">The draft royal decree amends Schedule Three of the Foreign Business Act 1999 to carve out one specific activity: agricultural futures trading conducted through designated futures trading centres where physical delivery of goods takes place. That activity will no longer require a foreign business licence in Thailand.</p>
<figure id="attachment_1002579" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-1002579" style="width: 1200px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="wp-image-1002579 size-full" src="https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/thailand-foreign-business-2.jpg" alt="Thailand eases foreign business red tape in eight sectors to cut regulatory overlap | News by Thaiger" width="1200" height="800" srcset="https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/thailand-foreign-business-2.jpg 1200w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/thailand-foreign-business-2-300x200.jpg 300w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/thailand-foreign-business-2-820x547.jpg 820w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/thailand-foreign-business-2-768x512.jpg 768w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-1002579" class="wp-caption-text">Deputy Government Spokesperson for the Prime Minister&#8217;s Office, Patdarasm Thongsaluaykorn | Photo via Thairath</figcaption></figure>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">The draft ministerial regulation lists eight service categories that foreign operators may carry out without a licence:</p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Telecommunications service businesses</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Treasury centre businesses</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Administrative, human resources, and IT management services</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Domestic debt-guarantee services</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Leasing of a partial space for electronic financial service machines and vending machines for company employees</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Petroleum drilling services</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Other businesses under securities and stock exchange law</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Agents, traders, advisers, or fund managers for derivatives contracts not governed by the Derivatives Act 2003</li>
</ol>
<h3 class="text-text-100 mt-3 -mb-1 text-[1.125rem] font-bold">Exemptions do not mean deregulation</h3>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Government Spokesperson Rachada Dhnadirek said the changes had been misrepresented in some reporting. The exempted categories either involve advanced technology or are already governed by dedicated legislation and closely supervised by state agencies.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">The changes are intended to remove duplicate approval steps, not to allow <a href="https://thethaiger.com/news/national/anutin-visits-surat-thani-over-thai-nominee-business-crackdown" target="_blank" rel="noopener">unsupervised foreign operation</a>. She said the purpose is to improve investment flexibility and bring regulations in line with the modern economic context.</p>
<figure id="attachment_1002581" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-1002581" style="width: 1200px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="wp-image-1002581 size-full" src="https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/thailand-foreign-business-3.jpg" alt="Thailand eases foreign business red tape in eight sectors to cut regulatory overlap | News by Thaiger" width="1200" height="800" srcset="https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/thailand-foreign-business-3.jpg 1200w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/thailand-foreign-business-3-300x200.jpg 300w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/thailand-foreign-business-3-820x547.jpg 820w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/thailand-foreign-business-3-768x512.jpg 768w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-1002581" class="wp-caption-text">Government Spokesperson Rachada Dhnadirek | Photo via <a href="https://www.thaigov.go.th/en/home">Royal Thai Government</a></figcaption></figure>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Each exempted category remains subject to its existing sectoral regulator. Telecommunications businesses fall under the National Broadcasting and Telecommunications Commission (NBTC). Treasury centre businesses remain subject to <a href="https://thethaiger.com/news/national/bank-of-thailand-to-roll-out-new-50-and-100-baht-polymer-banknotes" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Bank of Thailand</a> oversight. Securities and derivatives businesses are supervised by the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC), and petroleum drilling continues to be governed by energy law.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Rachada also confirmed that software development had been dropped from the draft ministerial regulation following concerns from relevant agencies about potential <a href="https://thethaiger.com/news/national/thailand-signs-deal-canva-digital-learning" target="_blank" rel="noopener">impacts on Thailand&#8217;s digital industry</a>. The Commerce Ministry removed the category to balance investment promotion with protection for domestic operators.</p>
<p>The story <a href="https://thethaiger.com/news/business/thailand-eases-foreign-business-rules-in-eight-sectors">Thailand eases foreign business red tape in eight sectors to cut regulatory overlap</a> as seen on <a href="https://thethaiger.com/">Thaiger News</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
			</item>
