					<description><![CDATA[<p>A Royal Thai dress exhibition has opened in Paris under the patronage of Princess Sirivannavari Nariratana Rajakanya, presenting royal garments, Thai textiles and contemporary designs at the Musée des Arts Décoratifs. The exhibition, La Mode en Majesté: Royal Thai Dress From Tradition to Modernity, opened today, May 13, and will run until November 1, 2026, &#8230;</p>
<p>The story <a href="https://thethaiger.com/news/national/royal-thai-garments-paris-exhibition">Royal Thai garments take centre stage at Paris exhibition</a> as seen on <a href="https://thethaiger.com/">Thaiger News</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<figure><img src="https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-2026-05-13T144746.827.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="Royal Thai garments take centre stage at Paris exhibition | Thaiger" style="margin-bottom: 15px;" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-2026-05-13T144746.827.jpg 1280w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-2026-05-13T144746.827-300x169.jpg 300w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-2026-05-13T144746.827-820x461.jpg 820w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-2026-05-13T144746.827-768x432.jpg 768w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-2026-05-13T144746.827-390x220.jpg 390w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" width="1280" height="720" /><figcaption>Royal Thai garments take centre stage at Paris exhibition<span class="copyright">Legacy</span></figcaption></figure><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1280" height="720" src="https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-2026-05-13T144746.827.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="Royal Thai garments take centre stage at Paris exhibition | Thaiger" style="float:right; margin:0 0 10px 10px;" srcset="https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-2026-05-13T144746.827.jpg 1280w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-2026-05-13T144746.827-300x169.jpg 300w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-2026-05-13T144746.827-820x461.jpg 820w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-2026-05-13T144746.827-768x432.jpg 768w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-2026-05-13T144746.827-390x220.jpg 390w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /><p>A <strong>Royal Thai dress exhibition</strong> has opened in Paris under the patronage of <a href="https://thethaiger.com/news/national/princess-sirivannavari-leads-thai-fabric-and-craft-competition" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Princess Sirivannavari</a> Nariratana Rajakanya, presenting <strong>royal garments</strong>, Thai textiles and contemporary designs at the <strong>Musée des Arts Décoratifs</strong>.</p>
<p>The exhibition, <em>La Mode en Majesté: Royal Thai Dress From Tradition to Modernity</em>, opened today, May 13, and will run until November 1, 2026, in Paris, France.</p>
<figure id="attachment_1002573" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-1002573" style="width: 1280px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-1002573" src="https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-2026-05-13T144759.526.jpg" alt="Royal Thai garments are being displayed in Paris as part of an exhibition on Thai dress, textiles and craftwork running until November 1." width="1280" height="720" srcset="https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-2026-05-13T144759.526.jpg 1280w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-2026-05-13T144759.526-300x169.jpg 300w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-2026-05-13T144759.526-820x461.jpg 820w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-2026-05-13T144759.526-768x432.jpg 768w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-2026-05-13T144759.526-390x220.jpg 390w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-1002573" class="wp-caption-text">Photo via HRH Princess Sirivannavari Nariratana Rajakanya</figcaption></figure>
<p>It is organised through cooperation between the Sustainable Arts and Crafts Institute of Thailand (SACIT), the Queen Sirikit Museum of Textiles, the Royal Thai Embassy in Paris and the <a href="https://madparis.fr/La-mode-en-majeste-Royal-Thai-dress-from-tradition-to-modernity" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Musée des Arts Décoratifs</a>.</p>
<p>The exhibition marks two diplomatic milestones between <a href="https://thethaiger.com/news/national/thailand-and-france-forge-future-partnerships" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Thailand and France</a>. These include 340 years of Thai-French diplomatic relations and 170 years since the formal establishment of diplomatic ties in 1856.</p>
<p>More than 200 items are displayed across seven exhibition rooms. The collection includes royal garments, dresses, accessories, ancient brocade textiles, traditional Thai craftwork and contemporary pieces by Thai designers.</p>
<figure id="attachment_1002576" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-1002576" style="width: 1280px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-1002576" src="https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-2026-05-13T145234.711.jpg" alt="Royal Thai garments are being displayed in Paris as part of an exhibition on Thai dress, textiles and craftwork running until November 1." width="1280" height="720" srcset="https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-2026-05-13T145234.711.jpg 1280w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-2026-05-13T145234.711-300x169.jpg 300w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-2026-05-13T145234.711-820x461.jpg 820w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-2026-05-13T145234.711-768x432.jpg 768w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-2026-05-13T145234.711-390x220.jpg 390w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-1002576" class="wp-caption-text">Photo via HRH Princess Sirivannavari Nariratana Rajakanya</figcaption></figure>
<p>The display also features garments designed by French designer Pierre Balmain in collaboration with Lesage, the French embroidery house known for haute couture craftsmanship. Works by Thai designers are also included.</p>
<p>The Royal Thai dress exhibition focuses on the development of royal court dress and the role of clothing as a form of cultural presentation on the international stage.</p>
<p>Among the items on display are royal garments worn by <a href="https://thethaiger.com/thai-life/mother-of-the-nation-queen-sirikits-influence-and-why-she-was-beloved" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Queen Sirikit, the Queen Mother</a>, Queen Suthida and Princess Sirivannavari.</p>
<figure id="attachment_1002575" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-1002575" style="width: 1280px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-1002575" src="https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-2026-05-13T145300.491.jpg" alt="Royal Thai garments are being displayed in Paris as part of an exhibition on Thai dress, textiles and craftwork running until November 1." width="1280" height="720" srcset="https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-2026-05-13T145300.491.jpg 1280w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-2026-05-13T145300.491-300x169.jpg 300w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-2026-05-13T145300.491-820x461.jpg 820w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-2026-05-13T145300.491-768x432.jpg 768w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-2026-05-13T145300.491-390x220.jpg 390w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-1002575" class="wp-caption-text">Photo via HRH Princess Sirivannavari Nariratana Rajakanya</figcaption></figure>
<p>The exhibition also presents the eight styles of chud Thai phra rajaniyom, or <a href="https://thethaiger.com/news/national/thai-princess-brings-royal-attire-to-europe-unesco" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Thai royal dress</a>. These are shown alongside Thai craftwork that reflects long-standing textile knowledge, design skills and cultural heritage.</p>
<p>Khaosod reported that the exhibition also supports Thailand’s plan to propose chud Thai phra rajaniyom for inclusion on UNESCO’s Lists of Intangible Cultural Heritage in 2026.</p>
<figure id="attachment_1002572" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-1002572" style="width: 1280px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-1002572" src="https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-2026-05-13T144832.468.jpg" alt="Royal Thai garments are being displayed in Paris as part of an exhibition on Thai dress, textiles and craftwork running until November 1." width="1280" height="720" srcset="https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-2026-05-13T144832.468.jpg 1280w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-2026-05-13T144832.468-300x169.jpg 300w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-2026-05-13T144832.468-820x461.jpg 820w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-2026-05-13T144832.468-768x432.jpg 768w, https://thethaiger.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/สำเนาของ-23-34-2026-05-13T144832.468-390x220.jpg 390w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-1002572" class="wp-caption-text">Photo via SACIT</figcaption></figure>
<p>In an earlier development, Thailand&#8217;s Ministry of Culture has formally proposed the <a href="https://thethaiger.com/news/national/thailand-nominates-traditional-dress-for-unesco-heritage-status" target="_blank" rel="noopener">traditional Thai costume</a>, chud Thai, as an intangible cultural heritage item for consideration by UNESCO. The proposal is reportedly set to be reviewed in 2026.</p>
<p>The story <a href="https://thethaiger.com/news/national/royal-thai-garments-paris-exhibition">Royal Thai garments take centre stage at Paris exhibition</a> as seen on <a href="https://thethaiger.com/">Thaiger News</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
			</item>
